{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869693506,"sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a15069a00146EWMsI74o0N57","messageID":"msg_d7a14c96600127jIFEojtmh0cZ","sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0f69a0da25514891ac79a288f50c9ffd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Project Infrastructure (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` with project configuration\n20:   - Project name: `kubectl-agentcube`\n21:   - Version: `0.1.0`\n22:   - Dependencies: `typer[all]>=0.9.0`, `pydantic>=2.0.0`, `pyyaml>=6.0`, `rich>=13.0.0`\n23:   - Dev dependencies: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`\n24:   - Console script: `kubectl-agentcube = agentcube.cli.main:app`\n25:   - File: `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n26:   - Verification: `pip install -e cmd/cli && kubectl-agentcube --help`\n27: \n28: - [ ] **T1.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py` with package exports\n29:   - Define `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n30:   - Export `app` from `agentcube.cli.main`\n31:   - Export `PackRuntime`, `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.runtime`\n32:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py`\n33:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube import __version__, app; print(__version__)\"`\n34: \n35: - [ ] **T1.3**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py` as subpackage marker\n36:   - Empty file or docstring for CLI subpackage\n37:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py`\n38:   - Verification: `python -c \"import agentcube.cli\"`\n39: \n40: ### Phase 2: Models Layer (ST-2)\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py` as package marker\n43:   - Export `MetadataOptions` from `pack_models`\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py`\n45:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions\"`\n46: \n47: - [ ] **T2.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n48:   - Fields: `agent_name`, `language='python'`, `entrypoint`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`, `requirements_file`, `description`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port=8080`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`, `agent_endpoint`\n49:   - Method: `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> MetadataOptions`\n50:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n51:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions; m = MetadataOptions(); print(m.language)\"`\n52: \n53: ### Phase 3: Services Layer (ST-3)\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` with package docstring\n56:   - Export `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` from `metadata_service`\n57:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n58:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import AgentMetadata\"`\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T3.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `AgentMetadata` model\n61:   - Pydantic `BaseModel` with fields: `agent_name`, `description`, `language='python'`, `entrypoint`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `requirements_file='requirements.txt'`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment`\n62:   - Validators: `validate_language` (python/java), `validate_build_mode` (local/cloud), `validate_port` (1-65535)\n63:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n64:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import AgentMetadata; m = AgentMetadata(agent_name='test', entrypoint='python main.py'); print(m.language)\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T3.3**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n67:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n68:   - Method: `load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata` — try `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml` in order\n69:   - Method: `save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Path` — save to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n70:   - YAML dump settings: `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n71:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n72:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService; print(MetadataService)\"`\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` with `DockerService` class\n75:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n76:   - Method: `check_docker_available(self) -> bool` — check Docker CLI availability\n77:   - Method: `build_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` — placeholder for AR-021\n78:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n79:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import DockerService; print(DockerService)\"`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 4: PackRuntime Core Logic (ST-4)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T4.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` with exports\n84:   - Export `PackRuntime` from `pack_runtime`\n85:   - Export `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.models`\n86:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n87:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime, MetadataOptions\"`\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T4.2**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime.__init__`\n90:   - Constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n91:   - Initialize: `self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)`\n92:   - Initialize: `self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)`\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import PackRuntime; r = PackRuntime(); print(r.verbose)\"`\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path)`\n97:   - Check `workspace_path.exists()` — raise `ValueError` if not\n98:   - Check `workspace_path.is_dir()` — raise `ValueError` if not\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n100:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_workspace_structure -v`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict) -> AgentMetadata`\n103:   - Try loading from `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml` (first match wins)\n104:   - If none exist: create new with defaults from options + workspace name\n105:   - Infer entrypoint if not provided: Python → `main.py` or first `.py` file; Java → `java -jar app.jar`\n106:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n107:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_load_or_create_metadata -v`\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict) -> AgentMetadata`\n110:   - Override `agent_name` if `options['agent_name']` provided\n111:   - Override `language` if `options['language']` provided\n112:   - Override `entrypoint` if `options['entrypoint']` provided\n113:   - Override `port` if `options['port']` provided\n114:   - Override `build_mode` if `options['build_mode']` provided\n115:   - Override `description` if `options['description']` provided\n116:   - Return updated metadata\n117:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n118:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_apply_option_overrides -v`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)`\n121:   - Python: check for at least one `.py` file — raise `ValueError` if missing\n122:   - Java: check for `pom.xml` — raise `ValueError` if missing\n123:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n124:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_validate_language_compatibility -v`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T4.7**: Implement `PackRuntime._process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)`\n127:   - Python: check `requirements.txt` exists (warning if missing, continue)\n128:   - Java: no additional processing (pom.xml handles dependencies)\n129:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n130:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_process_dependencies -v`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T4.8**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]`\n133:   - If `Dockerfile` exists: return path (no regeneration)\n134:   - If missing: generate based on `metadata.language`\n135:   - Python template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, pip install, expose port\n136:   - Java template: multi-stage Maven build → JRE runtime\n137:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n138:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_dockerfile -v`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.9**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str`\n141:   - Template: `FROM python:3.10-slim`, `WORKDIR /app`, `COPY requirements.txt`, `RUN pip install`, `COPY .`, `EXPOSE {port}`, `CMD [{entrypoint}]`\n142:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n143:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_python_dockerfile -v`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T4.10**: Implement `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str`\n146:   - Template: Multi-stage with `maven:3.8-openjdk-17` build → `openjdk:17-slim` runtime\n147:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n148:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_generate_java_dockerfile -v`\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T4.11**: Implement `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path])`\n151:   - Set `metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}` if dockerfile exists\n152:   - Save metadata via `self._metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n153:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n154:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_update_pack_metadata -v`\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.12**: Implement `PackRuntime.pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n157:   - Execute full workflow: validate → load metadata → apply overrides → validate language → process deps → generate dockerfile → update metadata\n158:   - Return dict: `{\"agent_name\", \"workspace_path\", \"metadata_path\", \"dockerfile_path\", \"status\"}`\n159:   - Catch exceptions: set `status=\"error\"` and raise\n160:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n161:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_full_workflow -v`\n162: \n163: ### Phase 5: CLI Command Layer (ST-5)\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T5.1**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` with Typer app setup\n166:   - Create `app = typer.Typer(help=\"AgentCube CLI for agent lifecycle management\")`\n167:   - Create `console = Console()` from Rich\n168:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n169:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube --help`\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `_handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool)` helper\n172:   - Print `[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]`\n173:   - Print traceback if `verbose=True`\n174:   - Exit with `typer.Exit(1)`\n175:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n176:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_handle_error -v`\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `pack()` command with all CLI options\n179:   - Options: `--workspace/-f` (default \".\"), `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n180:   - Resolve `workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()`\n181:   - Build `options` dict from CLI arguments\n182:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n183:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube pack --help`\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `pack()` command execution with progress spinner\n186:   - Use `rich.progress.Progress` with `SpinnerColumn`, `TextColumn`\n187:   - Create `PackRuntime(verbose)` and call `runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)`\n188:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n189:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_command_execution -v`\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `pack()` command success output formatting\n192:   - Print: `[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{agent_name}[/bold] packed`\n193:   - Print: `Workspace: {path}`, `Metadata: {path}`, `Dockerfile: {path}`\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n195:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_success_output -v`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `pack()` command error handling with `_handle_error`\n198:   - Wrap `PackRuntime.pack()` in try-except\n199:   - Call `_handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)` on exception\n200:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n201:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_pack_cli.py::test_pack_error_handling -v`\n202: \n203: ### Phase 6: Example Workspaces (ST-6)\n204: \n205: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py` example agent