ta Spec: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Describe CLI pack command functionality]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: [TO BE FILLED]\n\nThe system SHALL provide [TO BE FILLED].\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869693485,"end":1775869693509}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775869693528,"sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a150e460016DV2sMKuF8rEku","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a14c96600127jIFEojtmh0cZ","sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":16145,"input":15906,"output":188,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":51}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775869698821,"sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a152303001iAi4LaoqM1r0gz","messageID":"msg_d7a150e78001rJIrnYEPbYgFHU","sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869706052,"sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","part":{"id":"prt_d7a153ee3001z3KRkMFo3fL45U","messageID":"msg_d7a150e78001rJIrnYEPbYgFHU","sessionID":"ses_285ebad56ffeDbH0G4AG4R8HWw","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-585d5430233e46e6a7a4d21edb23caf4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                           Developer Environment                          │\n24: │  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐               │\n25: │  │   Terminal   │───▶│  kubectl-    │───▶│  Workspace   │               │\n26: │  │   (CLI)      │    │  agentcube   │    │  Directory   │               │\n27: │  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘               │\n28: │                              │                                           │\n29: │                              ▼                                           │\n30: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n31: │                    │ agent_metadata.  │                                  │\n32: │                    │ yaml             │                                  │\n33: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n34: │                              │                                           │\n35: │                              ▼                                           │\n36: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n37: │                    │ Dockerfile       │ (generated if missing)           │\n38: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Component Diagram\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                         agentcube/cli/main.py                            │\n47: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n48: │  │                        Typer App                                  │   │\n49: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  │   │\n50: │  │  │   pack()   │  │   build()  │  │  publish() │  │  invoke()  │  │   │\n51: │  │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │   │\n52: │  │  └─────┬──────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  │   │\n53: │  └───────│──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n54: │          │                                                               │\n55: └──────────│───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n56:            ▼\n57: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n58: │                      agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py                   │\n59: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n60: │  │                      PackRuntime                                  │   │\n61: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n62: │  │  │   pack()        │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_load_or_create_ │   │   │\n63: │  │  │   (main entry)  │  │workspace_        │  │metadata()       │   │   │\n64: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │structure()       │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n65: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n66: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n67: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n68: │  │  │_apply_option_   │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_process_       │   │   │\n69: │  │  │overrides()      │  │language_         │  │dependencies()   │   │   │\n70: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │compatibility()   │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n71: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n72: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n73: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n74: │  │  │_generate_       │──▶│_update_pack_    │──▶│_prepare_output_ │   │   │\n75: │  │  │dockerfile()     │  │metadata()       │  │path()           │   │   │\n76: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n77: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n78: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n79:            │\n80:            ▼\n81: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │                      agentcube/services/                                 │\n83: │  ┌───────────────────────┐        ┌───────────────────────┐            │\n84: │  │   MetadataService     │        │     DockerService     │            │\n85: │  │  (metadata_service.py)│        │  (docker_service.py)  │            │\n86: │  │  - load_metadata()    │        │  - check_docker_      │            │\n87: │  │  - save_metadata()    │        │    available()        │            │\n88: │  │  - validate_workspace │        │  - build_image()      │            │\n89: │  └───────────────────────┘        └───────────────────────┘            │\n90: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n91:            │\n92:            ▼\n93: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n94: │                      agentcube/models/pack_models.py                     │\n95: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n96: │  │                    MetadataOptions                                │   │\n97: │  │  - agent_name: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n98: │  │  - language: Optional[str] = 'python'                             │   │\n99: │  │  - entrypoint: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n100: │  │  - port: Optional[int] = 8080                                     │   │\n101: │  │  - build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'                            │   │\n102: │  │  - description: Optional[str]                                     │   │\n103: │  │  - from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])                     │   │\n104: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n105: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### Request Flow\n109: \n110: ```\n111: User                    CLI (main.py)              PackRuntime           Services\n112:  │                          │                          │                    │\n113:  │ kubectl-agentcube pack   │                          │                    │\n114:  │─────────────────────────▶│                          │                    │\n115:  │                          │ PackRuntime(verbose)     │                    │\n116:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n117:  │                          │                          │                    │\n118:  │                          │ pack(workspace, options) │                    │\n119:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n120:  │                          │                          │                    │\n121:  │                          │                          │ _validate_workspace│\n122:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n123:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n124:  │                          │                          │                    │\n125:  │                          │                          │ _load_or_create    │\n126:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n127:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n128:  │                          │                          │  AgentMetadata     │\n129:  │                          │                          │                    │\n130:  │                          │                          │ _apply_overrides   │\n131:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n132:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n133:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n134:  │                          │                          │  merged metadata   │\n135:  │                          │                          │                    │\n136:  │                          │                          │ _validate_language │\n137:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n138:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n139:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n140:  │                          │                          │                    │\n141:  │                          │                          │ _process_deps      │\n142:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n143:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n144:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n145:  │                          │                          │                    │\n146:  │                          │                          │ _generate_dockerfile\n147:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n148:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n149:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n150:  │                          │                          │  Dockerfile path   │\n151:  │                          │                          │                    │\n152:  │                          │                          │ _update_pack_metadata\n153:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n154:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n155:  │                          │                          │                    │\n156:  │                          │◀─────────────────────────│                    │\n157:  │                          │  result dict             │                    │\n158:  │                          │                          │                    │\n159:  │◀─────────────────────────│                          │                    │\n160:  │  Success message with    │                          │                    │\n161:  │  agent_name, paths       │                          │                    │\n162:  │                          │                          │                    │\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Data Structures\n168: \n169: ### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n173: from typing import Optional, Any, Dict\n174: \n175: @dataclass\n176: class MetadataOptions:\n177:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n178:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n179:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n180:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n181:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n182:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n183:     description: Optional[str] = None\n184:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n185:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n186:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n187:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n188:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n189:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n190:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n191:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n192: \n193:     @classmethod\n194:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n195:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### `AgentMetadata` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n202: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n203: \n204: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n205:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n206:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n207:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n208:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n209:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n210:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n211:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n212:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n213:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n214:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n215:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n216:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n217:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n218:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n219:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n220:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n221:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n222:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n223:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n224:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n225:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n226:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n227: \n228:     @field_validator('language')\n229:     @classmethod\n230:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n231:         allowed = ['python', 'java']\n232:         v_lower = v.lower()\n233:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n234:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n235:         return v_lower\n236: \n237:     @field_validator('build_mode')\n238:     @classmethod\n239:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n240:         allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n241:         v_lower = v.lower()\n242:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n243:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n244:         return v_lower\n245: \n246:     @field_validator('port')\n247:     @classmethod\n248:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n249:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n250:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n251:         return v\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: from pathlib import Path\n258: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n259: \n260: class PackRuntime:\n261:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n262:         self.verbose = verbose\n263:         self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n264:         self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n265: \n266:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n267:         result = {\n268:             \"agent_name\": None,\n269:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n270:             \"metadata_path\": None,\n271:             \"dockerfile_path\": None,\n272:             \"status\": \"pending\"\n273:         }\n274:         try:\n275:             self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n276:             metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n277:             metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n278:             self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n279:             self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n280:             dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n281:             self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n282:             output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n283:             \n284:             result[\"agent_name\"] = metadata.agent_name\n285:             result[\"metadata_path\"] = str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\")\n286:             result[\"dockerfile_path\"] = str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None\n287:             result[\"status\"] = \"success\"\n288:         except Exception as e:\n289:             result[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n290:             result[\"error\"] = str(e)\n291:             raise\n292:         return result\n293: \n294:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n295:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n296:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n297:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n298:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n299: \n300:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n301:         metadata_files = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n302:         for filename in metadata_files:\n303:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n304:             if filepath.exists():\n305:                 return self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n306:         \n307:         agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n308:         return AgentMetadata(\n309:             agent_name=agent_name,\n310:             language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n311:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, \"python\"),\n312:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n313:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n314:             description=options.get(\"description\", \"\")\n315:         )\n316: \n317:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n318:         updates = {}\n319:         if options.get(\"agent_name\"):\n320:             updates[\"agent_name\"] = options[\"agent_name\"]\n321:         if options.get(\"language\"):\n322:             updates[\"language\"] = options[\"language\"]\n323:         if options.get(\"entrypoint\"):\n324:             updates[\"entrypoint\"] = options[\"entrypoint\"]\n325:         if options.get(\"port\"):\n326:             updates[\"port\"] = options[\"port\"]\n327:         if options.get(\"build_mode\"):\n328:             updates[\"build_mode\"] = options[\"build_mode\"]\n329:         if options.get(\"description\"):\n330:             updates[\"description\"] = options[\"description\"]\n331:         \n332:         for key, value in updates.items():\n333:             setattr(metadata, key, value)\n334:         return metadata\n335: \n336:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n337:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n338:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n339:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n340:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n341: \n342:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n343:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n344:         if not py_files:\n345:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n346: \n347:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n348:         pom_file = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n349:         if not pom_file.exists():\n350:             raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in Java workspace\")\n351: \n352:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n353:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n354:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n355:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n356:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n357: \n358:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n359:         requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n360:         if requirements_file.exists():\n361:             pass\n362: \n363:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n364:         pass\n365: \n366:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n367:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n368:         if dockerfile_path.exists():\n369:             return dockerfile_path\n370:         \n371:         content = \"\"\n372:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n373:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n374:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n375:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n376:         \n377:         dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n378:         return dockerfile_path\n379: \n380:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n381:         return f'''FROM python:3.10-slim\n382: WORKDIR /app\n383: COPY requirements.txt .\n384: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n385: COPY . .\n386: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n387: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n388: '''\n389: \n390:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n391:         return f'''FROM maven:3.8-openjdk-17 as build\n392: WORKDIR /app\n393: COPY pom.xml .\n394: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n395: COPY . .\n396: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n397: FROM openjdk:17-slim\n398: WORKDIR /app\n399: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n400: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n401: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n402: '''\n403: \n404:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n405:         if dockerfile_path:\n406:             metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}\n407:         self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n408: \n409:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n410:         if output_path:\n411:             return Path(output_path)\n412:         return workspace_path / \"packaged\"\n413: \n414:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n415:         if language == \"python\":\n416:             main_py = workspace_path / \"main.py\"\n417:             if main_py.exists():\n418:                 return \"python, main.py\"\n419:             py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n420:             if py_files:\n421:                 return f\"python, {py_files[0].name}\"\n422:         elif language == \"java\":\n423:             return \"java, -jar, app.jar\"\n424:         return \"\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## API Contracts\n430: \n431: ### Command Interface\n432: \n433: | Command | Arguments | Description |\n434: |---------|-----------|-------------|\n435: | `pack` | `-f/--workspace` (default: `.`) | Path to agent workspace directory |\n436: | | `--agent-name` | Override agent name (Optional) |\n437: | | `--language` | Programming language: python, java (Optional) |\n438: | | `--entrypoint` | Override entrypoint command (Optional) |\n439: | | `--port` | Port to expose in Dockerfile (Optional, int) |\n440: | | `--build-mode` | Build strategy: local or cloud (Optional) |\n441: | | `--description` | Agent description (Optional) |\n442: | | `--output` | Output path for packaged workspace (Optional) |\n443: | | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging (bool, default: False) |\n444: \n445: ### Typer Command Signature\n446: \n447: ```python\n448: @app.command()\n449: def pack(\n450:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n451:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n452:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n453:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n454:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n455:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n456:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n457:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n458:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n459: ) -> None:\n460:     \"\"\"Validate and prepare agent workspace for building.\"\"\"\n461:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n462:     \n463:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n464:     options = {\n465:         \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n466:         \"language\": language,\n467:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n468:         \"port\": port,\n469:         \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n470:         \"description\": description,\n471:         \"output\": output,\n472:     }\n473:     \n474:     try:\n475:         with Progress(\n476:             SpinnerColumn(),\n477:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n478:         ) as progress:\n479:             task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n480:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose)\n481:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n482:         \n483:         console.print(f\"[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold] packed.\")\n484:         console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n485:         console.print(f\"  Metadata:  {result['metadata_path']}\")\n486:         if result['dockerfile_path']:\n487:             console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n488:     except Exception as e:\n489:         _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Metadata File Format\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: agent_name: my-agent\n496: description: Example agent\n497: language: python\n498: entrypoint: python, main.py\n499: port: 8080\n500: build_mode: local\n501: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n502: version: null\n503: image:\n504:   dockerfile_path: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ## Error Handling\n510: \n511: ### Exit Codes\n512: \n513: | Code | Condition | Error Message |\n514: |------|-----------|---------------|\n515: | `1` | Workspace does not exist | `Workspace directory does not exist: {path}` |\n516: | `1` | Workspace is not a directory | `Workspace path is not a directory: {path}` |\n517: | `1` | No Python files in workspace | `No Python files found in workspace` |\n518: | `1` | No pom.xml in Java workspace | `No pom.xml found in Java workspace` |\n519: | `1` | Invalid language | Pydantic validation error |\n520: | `1` | Invalid build_mode | Pydantic validation error |\n521: | `1` | Invalid port range | Pydantic validation error |\n522: | `1` | PackRuntime.pack raises | `Error packaging agent: {e}` (with traceback if verbose) |\n523: \n524: ### Error Handler Implementation\n525: \n526: ```python\n527: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n528:     from rich.console import Console\n529:     console = Console()\n530:     \n531:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n532:     if verbose:\n533:         import traceback\n534:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n535:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## Testing Strategy\n541: \n542: ### Unit Tests\n543: \n544: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n545: |-----------|-------|----------|\n546: | `test_pack_valid_python_workspace` | Valid Python workspace with main.py | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n547: | `test_pack_valid_java_workspace` | Valid Java workspace with pom.xml | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n548: | `test_pack_missing_workspace` | Non-existent path | ValueError \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n549: | `test_pack_not_directory` | File path instead of directory | ValueError \"Workspace path is not a directory\" |\n550: | `test_pack_python_no_py_files` | Directory with no .py files | ValueError \"No Python files found\" |\n551: | `test_pack_java_no_pom` | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError \"No pom.xml found\" |\n552: | `test_pack_override_agent_name` | `--agent-name custom-name` | metadata.agent_name == \"custom-name\" |\n553: | `test_pack_override_language` | `--language java` | metadata.language == \"java\" |\n554: | `test_pack_override_port` | `--port 9000` | metadata.port == 9000 |\n555: | `test_pack_invalid_language` | `--language ruby` | Pydantic validation error |\n556: | `test_pack_invalid_port` | `--port 70000` | Pydantic validation error \"port must be 1-65535\" |\n557: | `test_pack_existing_dockerfile` | Workspace with pre-existing Dockerfile | Dockerfile not regenerated, path returned |\n558: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_python` | Python workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Python template |\n559: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_java` | Java workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Java template |\n560: | `test_pack_metadata_fallback` | Workspace with agent.yaml (no agent_metadata.yaml) | Loads from agent.yaml |\n561: \n562: ### Integration Tests\n563: \n564: | Scenario | Description |\n565: |----------|-------------|\n566: | `test_pack_full_flow_python` | End-to-end: create temp Python workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n567: | `test_pack_full_flow_java` | End-to-end: create temp Java workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n568: | `test_pack_with_existing_metadata` | Workspace with agent_metadata.yaml → pack preserves and updates metadata |\n569: | `test_pack_cli_integration` | Run `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path` via subprocess, verify exit code and output |\n570: | `test_pack_verbose_output` | Pack with --verbose, verify detailed logs printed |\n571: | `test_pack_output_path` | Pack with --output /custom/path, verify packaged artifacts location |\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## File Structure\n576: \n577: ```\n578: cmd/cli/\n579: ├── pyproject.toml                  # Project metadata, dependencies, console scripts\n580: ├── agentcube/\n581: │   ├── __init__.py                 # Package version, exports app + runtimes\n582: │   ├── cli/\n583: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # CLI subpackage marker\n584: │   │   └ main.py                   # Typer app, pack command, _handle_error\n585: │   ├── models/\n586: │   │   └ pack_models.py            # MetadataOptions dataclass\n587: │   ├── runtime/\n588: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Re-exports PackRuntime + MetadataOptions\n589: │   │   └ pack_runtime.py           # PackRuntime class\n590: │   ├── services/\n591: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Services package docstring\n592: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py     # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n593: │   │   ├── docker_service.py       # DockerService (for build validation)\n594: │   ├── operations/\n595: │   │   └ __init__.py               # Placeholder (no symbols)\n596: ├── examples/\n597: │   ├── hello-agent/\n598: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n599: │   ├── math-agent/\n600: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n601: └── tests/\n602:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py        # PackRuntime unit tests\n603:     ├── test_pack_cli.py            # CLI pack command tests\n604:     └ test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n605: ```\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: ## Dependencies\n610: \n611: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n612: |---------|---------|---------|\n613: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework with Rich support |\n614: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation and serialization |\n615: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML metadata file parsing |\n616: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Progress spinner, colored output |\n617: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK (optional, for validation) |\n618: | `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n619: | `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mocking for unit tests |\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## Implementation Notes\n624: \n625: ### Metadata File Resolution Order\n626: \n627: The `pack` command loads metadata from files in this order (first match wins):\n628: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n629: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n630: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n631: \n632: If none exist, new metadata is created based on CLI options and workspace defaults.\n633: \n634: ### Entrypoint Inference\n635: \n636: When `--entrypoint` is not provided:\n637: - Python: Look for `main.py` → `\"python, main.py\"`; else first `.py` file → `\"python, {filename}\"`\n638: - Java: Default → `\"java, -jar, app.jar\"`\n639: \n640: ### Dockerfile Generation Logic\n641: \n642: 1. If `Dockerfile` exists in workspace → return existing path (no regeneration)\n643: 2. If missing → generate based on `metadata.language`:\n644:    - Python: Multi-stage with `pip install` from requirements.txt\n645:    - Java: Multi-stage Maven build → slim JRE runtime\n646: \n647: ### Metadata Save Format\n648: \n649: ```yaml\n650: # agent_metadata.yaml\n651: agent_name: my-agent\n652: description: \"Example agent\"\n653: language: python\n654: entrypoint: \"python, main.py\"\n655: port: 8080\n656: build_mode: local\n657: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n658: image:\n659:   dockerfile_path: ./Dockerfile\n660: ```\n661: \n662: YAML dump settings:\n663: - `default_flow_style=False`\n664: - `indent=2`\n665: - `sort_keys=False`\n666: - Exclude `None` fields: `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ## References\n671: \n672: - cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n673: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n674: - AR-021 — CLI build command (follows pack)\n675: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build)\n\n(End of file - total 675 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775869706038,"end":1775869706048}}}}
